00:16:49.480 --> 00:16:51.320
Yes, he’s awake, isn’t he?

00:16:53.280 --> 00:16:54.640
Let’s go, Sa.

00:16:55.200 --> 00:16:56.800
Oh, Kaew!

00:16:59.800 --> 00:17:02.440
Are you feeling better now?

00:17:03.520 --> 00:17:06.800
Ruedee, can you take me somewhere?

00:17:08.520 --> 00:17:09.480
Where?

00:17:45.520 --> 00:17:47.160
Finally, you came.

00:17:53.920 --> 00:17:57.320
What’s wrong, dear? Why are you here?

00:18:11.680 --> 00:18:14.640
Has he been following me from my past life?

00:18:15.760 --> 00:18:17.360
Past life, sir?

00:18:18.320 --> 00:18:20.000
Yes, because of a promise.

00:18:21.880 --> 00:18:23.120
A promise…

00:18:26.320 --> 00:18:29.160
What should I do to be free from it, Luangta?

00:18:31.080 --> 00:18:32.400
Atone for one’s sins.

00:18:34.200 --> 00:18:36.400
Can we do that, sir?

00:18:42.680 --> 00:18:44.920
Making merits in this life, to be together in the next.

00:18:45.360 --> 00:18:49.800
Is it true or just a belief that it would make us be together in every life?

00:18:54.280 --> 00:18:55.920
Keep making merits together,

00:18:56.520 --> 00:18:58.440
and maintain the same moral foundation.

00:18:59.160 --> 00:19:01.600
And you shall find each other, always.

00:19:02.160 --> 00:19:06.160
I see. So, it’s not just a belief then.

00:19:13.800 --> 00:19:17.680
Can I join you to make merits like this every day?

00:19:25.480 --> 00:19:27.760
No longer bound by promises.

00:19:29.960 --> 00:19:33.520
Never to see each other again, whether in this life…

00:19:35.040 --> 00:19:37.200
…or any other life.

00:19:40.240 --> 00:19:42.000
And be parted forever?

00:19:47.720 --> 00:19:48.560
No.

00:19:50.120 --> 00:19:52.040
I don’t want that.

00:19:54.160 --> 00:19:54.960
Kaew!

00:19:55.280 --> 00:19:57.120
Think about it carefully, dear.

00:20:04.560 --> 00:20:06.040
But deep down,

00:20:07.960 --> 00:20:10.000
